What do you purchase (Asset vs Business)?
FRS 103(R) Business Combinations determines if an acquired set of activities and assets is a business;
A business includes an input and a substantive process that together significantly contribute to the ability to create output. e.g. special knowledge and skills, (unlike operating pools in real estate, shipping industry).Optional fair values concentration test: concentrated in a single or a group of similar identifiable asset.
